      • 2 years labor

Product Description:
Oakworks Single Carbon Fiber Arm Board (6” wide) (42585)

The Oakworks Carbon fiber arm board is fully radiolucent with a 180° range of motion. The arm board requires no mounting or attachment hardware and simply slides under the table top pad. This product can be used on any fluoroscopy table and can support arms and feet in a variety of positioning configurations. This unique design allows the product to be folded together for safe and compact storage when not in use.

Product Description:
Oakworks Interventional Supine Pillow System (81821)

Oakworks Interventional Supine Pillow System supports patients neck in a position of comfort to reduce muscle spasm. It secures the cervical spine in either neutral or rotation. Head easily rotates to the opposite side of the injection with comfortable support of the ear and occiput. The dual resistive foam is designed to resist roll back and slightly raised position and beveled sides create a supportive yet unobstructed working space for the physicians

Product Description:
Oakworks Spine Positioning System II 

 

The Oakworks Spine Positioning System II is an integral component of the pain management suite.

The device improves visualization of the necessary anatomic landmarks for safe and accurate spinal injections. Designed to provide greater visualization of cervical, thoracic and lumbar spine including the cervicothoracic junction regardless of the patient's body habitus, the product solves imaging, stability and patient comfort issues associated with spine procedures. The system comes with portable case for clean transport and storage

 

Features

  • Integral component of the pain management suite
  • Improves visualization of the necessary anatomic landmarks for safe and accurate spinal injections
  • Solves imaging, stability and patient comfort issues associated with spine procedures
  • Design provides greater visualization of cervical, thoracic and lumbar spine including the cervicothoracic junction regardless of the patient's body habitus
  • Comes with portable case for clean transport and storage

 

 

Specification

  • Weight: 16 lbs
  • Weight Limit: 350 lbs
  • Frame with Face Rest: 12” x 32.5” (30 x 84 cm)
  • Crescent Face Pad: 12” (30 cm) Diameter
  • Contoured Torso Support Pad: 6.5” x 23” x 30” (17 x 58 x 76 cm)
  • Contoured Torso Wedge: 2” x 22” x 29” (5 x 56 x 74 cm)
  • Large Adjuster Pad: 8” x 22” x 2” (20 x 56 x 5 cm)
  • Small Adjuster Pad: 7” x 12” x 1.5” (18 x 30 x 4 cm)

Option Set: Oakworks Boiance Face Rest Crescent
Product Description:
Oakworks Boiance Face Rest Crescent

The Boiance™ Face Cradle Pillow difference is found in its water spheres within the multi-layer foam cushioning that supports the face and weight of the head. These spheres literally float the face. This sense of buoyancy created by the water spheres allows the Boiance™ Face cradle pillow to conform to the face much better than foam face rests. This unique design creates incredibly comfortable support your clients will love!

The Boiance™ Face Cradle Pillow also features a unique, very open space to avoid all pressure on the eyes and sinus cavities. Now your clients can lie face down for extended periods, and even open their eyes if there is an aesthetic element like a flower for them to gaze upon.

Description

The Oakworks CFPM300 c-arm/imaging table is our #1 best selling “diving board” style table.

The popular (3) movements offered by the CFM300 are the most commonly used in a Pain Mangement setting and when combined with Oakworks competitive pricing makes it a value that is hard to beat.

Imaging Features:
  • Carbon Fiber Top – 56 in. Metal free imaging space
  • Top Dimensions – 22 in. (56cm) wide x 84 in. (214cm) long – Integrated Headrest Version
  • Top Dimensions – 24 in. (61cm) wide x 80 in. (203cm) long – Rectangular Top Version
  • Motion 2 – Electric Trendelenburg tilt +15°/-12°
  • Motion 3 – Electric Lateral tilt ±15°
  • Controls – Multi-function hand control
  • Weight Capacity – 500 lb (227kg)
  • Product Weight – 475 lb (216kg)
  • Included Features – 1 in. (3cm) Radiolucent Comfort Foam™ table top pad, 4 in. (10cm) locking casters, Crescent face rest pad (included with integrated headrest top), patient safety straps (2)
  • Warranty – 1 years parts and labor
  • Safety Listings – CE marked, cETLus approved, CB Certificate
